Function : 
Function is a self contained block of statement.
Every function performs some specific task.

Advantages of function : 
1. Function reduces program size
2. Function reduces complexity
3. Function increases code reusability 
4. Function reduces redundancy of code
5. Function makes debugging easier
6. We can create n no. of functions 
7. A function can be called n no. of times

Types of functions : 

    a. Built-in function | In-built function | Standard function | Predefined function | Library function 
    Functions whose definition part is already defined
    Ex : write(), toFixed(), toPrecision() etc

    b. User-defined function : 
    Functions whose definition part is defined by the programmer according to its programming needs.

Categories of functions : 
    a. No argument No return type 
    b. No argument with return type 
    c. With argument no return type
    d. With argument and with return type 

Keypoints : 

1. Declaration is a specific syntax form (function name() {}).

2. Definition is a broader concept — any time you define a function, whether by declaration, expression, or arrow function.

3. So, all function declarations are function definitions, but not all function definitions are declarations.

4. function declaration --> function definition 
function demo(){
    .....
} 

5. function expression | anonymous function  
function(){
    ......
}

6. variable function
var demo = function(){
    ......
}
demo();

7. Lambda expression | Fat arrow function 
()=>{
    ...
} 

var demo = ()=>{
    ...
} 
demo(); 

8. Immediately Invoked arrow function(fat arrow function) 
(()=>{
    ....
    ....
})()

Immediately Invoked function expression 
(function(){
    ....
    ....
})()